Fish Ranking is a contest held periodically by the Fishermen's Guild. Participants compete based on a set of defined rules regarding the size and weight of a certain big fish.${prompt}

Value is determined by the calculation of “points” and evaluated based on the contest rules. For example, when the rules designate the “smallest fish,” the person with the fewest points will win.${prompt}

Just by looking at your smiling faces, I can tell you're all having a great time at this year's Sunbreeze Festival!
So, are you rrready for some music? I know we're ready to sing our hearrrts out!
Where in sweet Selbina could Mumor be!?
Oh well, the show must go on.
It's a little embarrassing to sing by myself, but any entertainer worth her miraclesalt would jump at this opporrrtunity.
This is my chance to go solo!
Everyone, feast your earrrs upon my astounding aria.
Your cacophonous warbling is enough to make me vacate the contents of my stomach.
These people are not stupid, either... They know that without your partner, you aren't even worth the stage on which you stand.
Who, indeed... Understandable, since I believe this is the first time I've deigned to grace you with my presence.
I am a diva. Does that appellation ring any bells for you, pray tell?
Oh, so you have indeed heard of my kind? No wonder you were once my master's favorite archfiend.
Though, in all truth, the title “archfiend” refers to nothing more than washed-up hacks who possess neither the drive nor the talent to reach for the stars...of divadom!
Yet now you've thrown even that away, settling for a mundane life of belching out dull drivel at vulgar venues.
Someone as wretched as you holds no value whatsoever.
I heard you associate with some upstart floozy who dares defy my master and dissuades archfiends from our cause. Do you know where she is?
Well, it seems you're all alone.
No matter. She'll simply have to wait until I'm finished with you.
Of course, someone of my sublime stature would never condescend to personally dispatch with a peon like you.
This minion should prove more than a sufficient substitute for accomplishing that task.
The crowd here may be raucous, but drown out its pesky din.♪
Now give yourself up to your dreams, just cast away your strife.★
Next, let your heavy eyelids fall and drool drip down your chin.♪
This soothing, tranquil lullaby leaves all bereft of life.★
Even without Mumor...I can cut this cocky diva down to size!
Hmph, it seems you may possess at least an iota of skill after all.
I'm not alone. I have the whole audience on my side!
Don't just stand there and take it, you invariably incompetent imbecile!
We must all work as one! Please, lend me your strrrength!
Ahahaha! Those earth tones truly do bring your outfit together, Uka.
You archfiends exist as nothing more than mere stepping stones on my path to glory!
It matters not how many enemies assail me. I can dispatch them all with but the bat of an eye!
You may now exit stage right. Oh, and I don't think you'll need to worry about any encores.
Fear not, I'll be sure to invite your friend to the after-party as well!
And so, without Mumor, Uka quickly succumbed to the diva and was banished to an interdimensional purgatory...
Be more supportive of her and you can overturn what has just transpired.
Band together and cheer on Uka to save her from the diabolical diva!
Haaah, haaah... I've got to hand it to you. I don't think I can beat you by myself.
If only Mumor were herrre, too.
Mumor? Oh, you mean that sorry excuse for a nemesis.
Just how might the addition of one more classless poseur change what is so obviously inevitable?
You certainly are persistent. My master must have seen...
But enough chatter! This time I shall truly send you off into eternal slumber with a special lullaby.
In the name of joy and happiness, I shall punish you!
Please forgive me, Uka. I tried oh-so-hard not to be late!
You see, I was in a meeting with the produc--
I mean, I took too long deciding what to wear. Teehee!
Hmmm? You must be hearing things.
She's a diva--one of Ullegore's songstrrresses--which means she has a much more talented voice than any of us forrrmer archfiends.
I'm sick and tired of Ullegore's lackeys trying to ruin our performances!
Ruin? Your act doesn't leave much to ruin.
Besides, this stage was built for a diva of my caliber, not amateurs such as yourselves.
H-how dare you! My sultry singing is the perfect complement to Uka's dynamic dancing, and that's why our popularity soars higher than any airship!
Think what you will. We shall see if you're still singing the same tune after I show you how to hold a true note.
How can the addition of one saucy starlet change the tide of battle so?
Mumor can absorrrb the energy from her cheerrring fans to unleash a devastating attack...
And when you add in Uka's Dancing Force...
Our power levels climb to over nine thousand!!!
P-power levels!? What sort of nonsense are you--
Let's play off this hoary old has-been before she even has a chance to butcher her swan song!
To see the inverted rainbow of your smile...
We'll dance to the abyss and back!
How nice to see you in such dire straits, Uka.
And I would hardly be a demon king if I didn't extend the same greeting to my archnemesis. Now would I, Mumor?
However, it won't do for me to lose one of my precious divas. We beg your leave...but shall depart regardless of your answer.
Don't you fret, my darling prima donna. We shall meet again, much to your chagrin.
Wherever there is a festival, I shall lurk amidst the shadows.
I shall bide my time until the glorious day when I can extinguish every last festive flame, enshrouding Vana'diel in a tenebrous mantle of tedium and ennui!
What a stunning performance, Mighty Maidens!
Next time, you mightaru want to <mumble-mumble>...
And ye best git some rest while ye still can!
You don't need to tell us that twice!
You three have rrreally grown into your roles as gof...er, managerrrs. Keep up the good work!
We are wholly undeserving of such lofty praise.
(We shall be the ones meting out empty compliments when Cream Puff's shining star eclipses you misnomered Mighty Maidens!)
Was that meant to be a backstage comment? Because even people all the way up in the gallery could hear it!
Y-yikes! No curtain call for us this time!!!
We're so grateful to you, our devoted and trustworthy fans, for coming out and supporting us!
That diva may have backed us into a corner, but with you all behind us, there was no way we could lose!
That dastardly Ullegore best watch his back, too! The Mighty Maidens will put a stop to his tyranny of tedium once and for all!
